race.comment: CROSS TASMAN (10) has come back in terrific order and continues to elevate, narrowly denied last start when beaten a lip in his bid for four straight. He'll likely take a sit from the draw but will be hunting them down late. IT'S A KNOCKOUT (9) went better than the form guide suggests when resuming at the Gold Coast and should tighten right up second-up. Expect him to be right there to pounce when they straighten. FURIOUS (13) was an arrogant winner here last start, making a mid-race move and putting them away with plenty in reserve over 2000m. The slight query is the drop back to the mile, but if they adopt similar tactics he can absolutely win again. CAPTAIN FURAI (16) hasn't won for a long time but his fresh run here three weeks ago was strong, and he'll have come on from that - though the draw does him no favours. HELLSING (2) has been edged out narrowly in his past two and is worth another chance on the quick back-up.
